# Public repo language (ADR-0007) — enforced, not advisory

This is the **public ELv2 engine**. Product tiers, Marketplace pricing, and
commercial *feature* framing live in `privaci-commercial`.

## Hard gate (runs before GitHub)

Pre-commit **blocks the commit** when staged lines match banned patterns:

```bash
python scripts/check_public_repo_language.py --staged
```

CI runs a full scan of `src/privaci/`, key operator docs, and release notes plus
`--git-log 30` on commit messages. **`./scripts/ci-local.sh` includes both.**

If the guard fails, **fix the wording before committing** — do not push and fix later.

## Say this

- **Plugin contract** / **`privaci.plugins` hook** / **plugin package installed**
- **Community mode** vs **plugin-installed** behaviour
- **License-gated** (not `Growth+`, `Starter`, `Business`)

## Never add (in src, operator docs, release notes, commit messages)

- Product tier names (`Growth`, `Growth+`, `Starter`, `Business`, `Enterprise`)
- `AWS Marketplace`, `Marketplace subscription`, `all tiers`
- `commercial plugin`, `commercial hooks`, `commercial entitlement`
- `commercial layer` / `privaci-commercial` outside CLI install hints and exit-code docs

## Allowed exceptions (do not “fix” these)

- `docs/adr/*`, `docs/spikes/*` — explain the public/private split
- `docs/extending-privaci.md` — plugin authors
- CLI/errors/fallbacks install hints: “requires the commercial layer” (exit UX)
- `docs/error-codes.md` — exit `5`/`6` remediation
- Spec ids: `commercial-tier-contract`, `commercial_layer_present`

## Agent rule

Before **every** public-repo commit: run `--staged` (or full `ci-local.sh`). Scrub
violations in the same turn. Never defer to the user.
